To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 2,060,619.40
- Total Revenue = 3,397,619.40

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{2,060,619.40}{3,397,619.40} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.6065 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 60.65\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '60.65%'} }
```
